> A C++ Enum in CAPS is bad coding style. Have you seen Cpp Core Guidelines?

btw in this repo guidelines there are no constraint for this, and most enums use uppercase names (if we consider enum values as constants, this rule will apply "Constant names are all uppercase, and use `_` to separate words.")

@jonnygrant I already opened a PR for this: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/16018
